WEBVTT

00:07.167 --> 00:16.250
♪♪♪

00:20.167 --> 00:22.083
(Seagulls cry)

00:22.125 --> 00:26.000
♪♪♪

00:26.042 --> 00:27.876
(Footsteps crunch)

00:29.542 --> 00:31.250
- Show me.

00:31.292 --> 00:33.167
(Seagulls cry)

00:33.209 --> 00:39.667
♪♪♪

00:39.709 --> 00:42.626
Deckhand: Come on! Come on!

00:39.709 --> 00:42.626
Deckhand 2: Mast deployed!

00:42.667 --> 00:44.167
(Deckhands shout)

00:45.250 --> 00:46.792
- (Sighs)

00:47.792 --> 00:49.250
(Box lid squeaks)

00:49.292 --> 00:51.000
(Gun clanks)

00:52.626 --> 00:54.667
(Deckhands shout)

00:54.709 --> 01:03.709
♪♪♪

01:10.542 --> 01:13.751
- It's very wise of you, sir,

01:10.542 --> 01:13.751
sending an emissary.

01:15.209 --> 01:17.751
The Lake Walkers will come

01:15.209 --> 01:17.751
around. I'm optimistic.

01:17.792 --> 01:19.334
- Optimistic?

01:19.375 --> 01:21.959
- Yes, sir. We'll get things

01:19.375 --> 01:21.959
back on track.

01:22.000 --> 01:24.709
- And what of the Scots,

01:22.000 --> 01:24.709
the French, Harp's lot?!

01:24.751 --> 01:27.083
Still poaching our trade!

01:27.125 --> 01:29.334
If we had the vaguest notion

01:27.125 --> 01:29.334
where their camps are

01:29.375 --> 01:31.334
we could march on them,

01:29.375 --> 01:31.334
start weeding them out.

01:31.375 --> 01:32.876
(Knock at the door)

01:32.918 --> 01:34.876
Soldier: Ahem. Sir, we have

01:32.918 --> 01:34.876
spotted a sail on the horizon,

01:34.918 --> 01:36.292
a Company ship approaching.

01:36.334 --> 01:38.709
- A Company ship? You're sure?

01:38.751 --> 01:39.792
Soldier: Yes, sir.

01:39.834 --> 01:41.667
Looks like a Navy frigate.

01:41.709 --> 01:44.083
(Receding footsteps)

01:46.667 --> 01:49.751
- Why would the Company send

01:46.667 --> 01:49.751
a ship this late in the season?

01:53.375 --> 02:02.375
♪♪♪

02:06.042 --> 02:08.459
(Native singing)

02:08.500 --> 02:17.500
♪♪♪

02:23.709 --> 02:25.626
(Native singing)

02:25.667 --> 02:34.667
♪♪♪

02:42.417 --> 02:44.459
(Birds chirp, fire crackles)

02:44.500 --> 02:47.209
- Go to the camp,

02:44.500 --> 02:47.209
gather our men.

02:47.250 --> 02:48.500
We'll meet you in the town.

02:48.542 --> 02:50.417
- Why are we going

02:48.542 --> 02:50.417
to Fort James?

02:50.459 --> 02:52.834
Why do we not return to the

02:50.459 --> 02:52.834
Lake Walkers and fix this?

02:52.876 --> 02:55.292
- Because Machk is a fanatic

02:52.876 --> 02:55.292
and will never be our ally.

02:55.334 --> 02:56.584
Dimanche: I disagree.

02:56.626 --> 02:59.209
He sees you as a European,

02:56.626 --> 02:59.209
as a threat, Harp.

02:59.250 --> 03:01.584
I should go talk to him.

02:59.250 --> 03:01.584
I can gain his trust.

03:01.626 --> 03:04.167
Sokanon: Dimanche,

03:01.626 --> 03:04.167
Machk would kill you.

03:04.209 --> 03:07.000
- Things have changed.

03:04.209 --> 03:07.000
We have lost our army

03:07.042 --> 03:09.042
so we deal with

03:07.042 --> 03:09.042
Benton ourselves.

03:09.083 --> 03:11.083
- So that's why we're going

03:09.083 --> 03:11.083
to Fort James?

03:11.125 --> 03:13.125
- Benton's surrounded

03:11.125 --> 03:13.125
by soldiers.

03:13.167 --> 03:16.167
- Then we will kill his soldiers

03:13.167 --> 03:16.167
and then we will kill him.

03:16.209 --> 03:17.626
- You're serious?

03:17.667 --> 03:19.125
He has eighty armed men.

03:19.167 --> 03:20.292
There are only four of us.

03:20.334 --> 03:21.834
Even with our entire company--

03:21.876 --> 03:24.292
- Go get our men

03:21.876 --> 03:24.292
and meet me in Fort James.

03:24.334 --> 03:26.459
- In spring, more ships will

03:24.334 --> 03:26.459
arrive full of redcoats.

03:26.500 --> 03:28.459
This is a battle that

03:26.500 --> 03:28.459
can't be won.

03:28.500 --> 03:30.167
Michael: Not necessarily.

03:30.209 --> 03:32.250
A strike at the heart of the

03:30.209 --> 03:32.250
Company would send a message

03:32.292 --> 03:34.918
that we are a serious threat,

03:32.292 --> 03:34.918
that the Company's vulnerable.

03:34.959 --> 03:37.209
- When did this boy

03:34.959 --> 03:37.209
become one of us?

03:37.250 --> 03:38.417
We don't know him.

03:38.459 --> 03:40.250
He could slit our throats

03:38.459 --> 03:40.250
in our sleep.

03:40.292 --> 03:43.667
- You going to slit our

03:40.292 --> 03:43.667
throats, Michael?

03:43.709 --> 03:45.584
- Well, you never know.

03:45.626 --> 03:48.709
- This obsession you have

03:45.626 --> 03:48.709
with Benton,

03:48.751 --> 03:50.375
it got Samoset killed.

03:50.417 --> 03:51.584
It will get us killed!

03:51.626 --> 03:54.167
- (Violent head butt)

03:51.626 --> 03:54.167
- Harp!

03:54.209 --> 03:56.209
- I'm done!

03:56.250 --> 03:58.209
I'm taking the men with me!

03:58.250 --> 04:07.083
♪♪♪

04:07.125 --> 04:08.500
(Birds chirp)

04:08.542 --> 04:10.626
(Knocking at door)

04:08.542 --> 04:10.626
Douglas: Mr. Grant?

04:10.667 --> 04:12.250
(Door opens)

04:14.667 --> 04:17.209
- Mr. Grant is indisposed.

04:17.250 --> 04:18.751
- I'll wait.

04:18.792 --> 04:21.209
(Petulant sigh)

04:18.792 --> 04:21.209
- You speak to me.

04:21.250 --> 04:23.792
- Why would I speak to you

04:21.250 --> 04:23.792
about my business?

04:23.834 --> 04:25.334
I had the police around.

04:25.375 --> 04:28.500
They were asking about

04:25.375 --> 04:28.500
Carruthers, how he died.

04:28.542 --> 04:30.584
I told them it was self-defense.

04:30.626 --> 04:32.083
- It was self-defense.

04:32.125 --> 04:35.167
- You killed the man

04:32.125 --> 04:35.167
in cold blood.

04:35.209 --> 04:36.792
- Well, he drew on me first.

04:36.834 --> 04:39.500
- Is Grant plannin' to murder

04:36.834 --> 04:39.500
all of the competition?

04:39.542 --> 04:41.918
This is no way to do business.

04:41.959 --> 04:43.834
- Hmm.

04:43.876 --> 04:46.626
We have news from up North

04:43.876 --> 04:46.626
regarding your brothers.

04:46.667 --> 04:47.918
(Glass clinks, liquor pours)

04:47.959 --> 04:50.167
- What about them?

04:47.959 --> 04:50.167
Pond: Hmm...

04:50.209 --> 04:51.751
Brother Cedric...

04:53.918 --> 04:55.876
Well, he's dead,

04:55.918 --> 05:00.209
the result apparently of a

04:55.918 --> 05:00.209
drunken brawl in Fort James.

05:00.250 --> 05:01.792
- Who told you this?

05:01.834 --> 05:04.000
- Some foul little voyageur

05:04.042 --> 05:06.375
recently returned

05:04.042 --> 05:06.375
from the frontier.

05:07.959 --> 05:10.209
- I donna believe it.

05:07.959 --> 05:10.209
- Oh, there's more.

05:10.250 --> 05:12.459
Brother Malcolm has gone to war.

05:12.500 --> 05:14.459
Instead of wooing

05:12.500 --> 05:14.459
the Lake Walker tribe,

05:14.500 --> 05:16.417
he's fighting them.

05:16.459 --> 05:19.792
- Lies. Malcolm would never

05:16.459 --> 05:19.792
jeopardize our business.

05:19.834 --> 05:21.626
- I hope that's true,

05:22.876 --> 05:24.292
for your sake,

05:24.334 --> 05:26.125
because if that is true

05:26.167 --> 05:28.959
and he is failing to secure

05:26.167 --> 05:28.959
the Lake Walker trade...

05:29.000 --> 05:30.918
Well, my friend,

05:30.959 --> 05:34.209
there's a very serious

05:30.959 --> 05:34.209
problem for you,

05:34.250 --> 05:36.584
and you saw firsthand

05:36.626 --> 05:38.792
how I deal with our problems.

05:45.876 --> 05:47.959
Oh, there's a woman um...

05:48.000 --> 05:51.667
Mr. Grant would like you

05:48.000 --> 05:51.667
to speak to Carruthers' widow.

05:51.709 --> 05:54.417
Yeah, his operation is small,

05:51.709 --> 05:54.417
but it's very lucrative.

05:54.459 --> 05:57.417
Mr. Grant would like

05:54.459 --> 05:57.417
to make her an offer.

05:57.459 --> 05:59.959
- First he kills the man,

06:00.000 --> 06:02.500
then he takes his company.

06:02.542 --> 06:04.834
- Well, it's just good business.

06:09.542 --> 06:10.626
(Door creaks shut)

06:10.667 --> 06:19.667
♪♪♪

06:24.667 --> 06:26.626
Chesterfield: It's a relief,

06:24.667 --> 06:26.626
isn't it?

06:26.667 --> 06:30.334
That moment you set foot again

06:26.667 --> 06:30.334
on solid ground.

06:30.375 --> 06:32.876
- You're Captain Chesterfield,

06:30.375 --> 06:32.876
I suppose?

06:32.918 --> 06:34.792
- I am. And you are?

06:34.834 --> 06:36.250
- Captain Benedict Johnson.

06:36.292 --> 06:38.709
I was expecting to be met

06:36.292 --> 06:38.709
at the jetty by Lord Benton.

06:38.751 --> 06:40.959
- We weren't lookin' for a ship,

06:38.751 --> 06:40.959
not this late in the season.

06:41.000 --> 06:42.334
You're lucky you beat the ice.

06:42.375 --> 06:44.375
- Nor was I looking to make

06:42.375 --> 06:44.375
the voyage,

06:44.417 --> 06:46.542
however circumstances have

06:44.417 --> 06:46.542
forced my urgent deployment

06:46.584 --> 06:48.792
to this miserable place.

06:48.834 --> 06:50.375
- Circumstances?

06:50.417 --> 06:52.375
- I must speak with Lord Benton

06:50.417 --> 06:52.375
straightaway.

06:52.417 --> 06:54.167
- Regardin' what, exactly?

06:54.209 --> 06:56.918
- I have orders from London,

06:54.209 --> 06:56.918
the Head Office,

06:56.959 --> 06:59.542
to be discussed

06:56.959 --> 06:59.542
with Lord Benton,

06:59.584 --> 07:01.751
not his subordinate.

07:01.792 --> 07:04.375
- Well, you'll see him tonight

07:01.792 --> 07:04.375
at dinner.

07:04.417 --> 07:06.292
In the meantime,

07:06.334 --> 07:08.918
his subordinate will buy you

07:06.334 --> 07:08.918
a fucking drink.

07:08.959 --> 07:12.250
- The town is--

07:08.959 --> 07:12.250
- This way.

07:12.292 --> 07:15.709
- I assume there's a place

07:12.292 --> 07:15.709
of worship here in Fort James?

07:15.751 --> 07:17.834
- Aye, the ale house.

07:17.876 --> 07:19.584
We're headed right for it.

07:19.626 --> 07:24.375
♪♪♪

07:24.417 --> 07:26.083
(Townspeople chatter)

07:31.500 --> 07:33.459
(Marching stomps)

07:34.626 --> 07:36.751
(Patrons chatter in French)

07:36.792 --> 07:39.542
- Sit there, table by the fire.

07:39.584 --> 07:41.375
(Door links shut)

07:41.417 --> 07:44.125
(Liquor pours, bottle thuds)

07:44.167 --> 07:46.542
- From the frigate?

07:44.167 --> 07:46.542
- His name's Johnson.

07:46.584 --> 07:48.667
Came out of fuckin' nowhere

07:46.584 --> 07:48.667
with a stick up his ass.

07:48.709 --> 07:50.334
Asked me where the church was.

07:50.375 --> 07:52.083
- Jesus Christ.

07:52.125 --> 07:54.209
Why is a senior officer

07:52.125 --> 07:54.209
suddenly showing up

07:54.250 --> 07:55.375
in Fort James unannounced?

07:55.417 --> 07:58.000
- Ah, don't worry.

07:55.417 --> 07:58.000
I can handle this prick.

07:58.042 --> 08:00.417
(Cup thuds)

08:00.459 --> 08:02.626
Go on, by the fire.

08:02.667 --> 08:04.292
I'll be right there.

08:04.334 --> 08:06.292
(Liquor pours)

08:06.334 --> 08:07.834
- Well, the prick is leaving.

08:07.876 --> 08:09.000
(Door opens)

08:09.042 --> 08:11.167
- Ah, where is he goin'?

08:09.042 --> 08:11.167
Fuck me!

08:11.209 --> 08:13.375
(Big slurp)

08:11.209 --> 08:13.375
(Cup bangs down)

08:13.417 --> 08:14.667
(Receding footsteps)

08:14.709 --> 08:16.083
(Fire crackles)

08:16.125 --> 08:17.918
(Wolf howls in distance)

08:18.959 --> 08:20.375
(Fire crackles)

08:22.083 --> 08:23.584
(Water laps gently)

08:27.375 --> 08:29.459
(Wolf howls in distance)

08:29.500 --> 08:33.834
♪♪♪

08:33.876 --> 08:35.709
(Firm tap)

08:35.751 --> 08:37.584
- Hm.

08:39.417 --> 08:41.334
- Can I trust you?

08:41.375 --> 08:43.125
(Fire crackles)

08:43.167 --> 08:47.918
♪♪♪

08:47.959 --> 08:50.959
- Of course you can trust me.

08:51.000 --> 08:54.000
- It's gonna be dangerous

08:51.000 --> 08:54.000
in Fort James.

08:55.125 --> 08:56.792
- I know.

08:58.709 --> 09:00.667
- And your girl, Clenna?

09:01.709 --> 09:05.083
When the spring comes and

09:01.709 --> 09:05.083
a ship departs for England,

09:05.125 --> 09:07.709
will you be on it?

09:07.751 --> 09:09.459
(Fire crackles)

09:09.500 --> 09:15.667
♪♪♪

09:15.709 --> 09:17.834
You have a decision to make.

09:17.876 --> 09:20.459
(Fire crackles)

09:20.500 --> 09:29.500
♪♪♪

09:32.250 --> 09:34.209
(Fire crackles)

09:34.250 --> 09:36.751
Benton: It's a shame you won't

09:34.250 --> 09:36.751
be able to stay long,

09:36.792 --> 09:38.000
(Cutlery clinks)

09:38.042 --> 09:40.000
if you're going to make it

09:38.042 --> 09:40.000
back to England

09:40.042 --> 09:41.542
before the ice comes.

09:41.584 --> 09:43.876
Chesterfield: A fortnight,

09:41.584 --> 09:43.876
I imagine.

09:43.918 --> 09:46.042
- I should think it was hardly

09:43.918 --> 09:46.042
worth your while

09:46.083 --> 09:48.417
coming all this way.

09:48.459 --> 09:50.083
- Game, is it?

09:50.125 --> 09:52.000
- Caribou.

09:52.042 --> 09:54.834
It's rather tough,

09:52.042 --> 09:54.834
but quite delicious,

09:54.876 --> 09:56.709
don't you think?

09:56.751 --> 09:58.334
(Hard gulp)

09:58.375 --> 09:59.626
(Cutlery clanks down)

09:59.667 --> 10:02.959
- Lord Fisher sends his regards,

10:03.000 --> 10:05.042
although I think he was

10:03.000 --> 10:05.042
rather surprised

10:05.083 --> 10:07.083
at your hasty departure

10:05.083 --> 10:07.083
from London,

10:07.125 --> 10:09.542
and without proper

10:07.125 --> 10:09.542
authorization.

10:09.584 --> 10:11.542
- Nonsense.

10:11.584 --> 10:13.959
Fisher had full knowledge

10:11.584 --> 10:13.959
of my plans.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.918
- It seems you are misinformed,

10:14.000 --> 10:16.918
Captain.

10:16.959 --> 10:19.000
- In any case,

10:19.042 --> 10:21.667
Lord Fisher is anxious

10:19.042 --> 10:21.667
to hear of your progress.

10:21.709 --> 10:24.167
He has asked for a full report.

10:24.209 --> 10:26.042
- Has he indeed?

10:26.083 --> 10:28.584
- Mmm. What strides have

10:26.083 --> 10:28.584
you made in your dealings

10:28.626 --> 10:32.042
with the Montreal upstarts,

10:28.626 --> 10:32.042
with Declan Harp,

10:32.083 --> 10:33.876
the inland wars, the Natives?

10:33.918 --> 10:36.083
Have you, for example,

10:33.918 --> 10:36.083
increased profits

10:36.125 --> 10:38.000
via an expansion of trade?

10:38.042 --> 10:40.250
- You may count yourself lucky,

10:38.042 --> 10:40.250
Johnson.

10:40.292 --> 10:43.042
You will be able to paint

10:40.292 --> 10:43.042
an entirely rosy picture

10:43.083 --> 10:44.459
on your return.

10:44.500 --> 10:47.584
- This man literally saved

10:44.500 --> 10:47.584
the Company!

10:47.626 --> 10:51.584
Lord Fisher should throw him

10:47.626 --> 10:51.584
a fucking parade!

10:51.626 --> 10:55.542
- I admit I was rather taken

10:51.626 --> 10:55.542
aback at the state of the town.

10:55.584 --> 10:58.876
I do hope you are providing

10:55.584 --> 10:58.876
a proper Christian example

10:58.918 --> 11:00.959
in this New World?

11:01.000 --> 11:02.876
The ale house, for instance,

11:02.918 --> 11:04.792
rather disturbing.

11:04.834 --> 11:07.500
Benton: But crucial for morale.

11:07.542 --> 11:09.500
It's a common error.

11:09.542 --> 11:12.375
You have just arrived

11:09.542 --> 11:12.375
in the New World, Captain.

11:12.417 --> 11:14.167
You'll learn.

11:14.209 --> 11:16.667
- (Sniffs, clears his throat)

11:16.709 --> 11:20.667
You've been very kind,

11:16.709 --> 11:20.667
but I must see to my men.

11:23.500 --> 11:26.667
Uh, I'll bring the girl ashore

11:23.500 --> 11:26.667
in the morning.

11:26.709 --> 11:28.292
- Oh yes?

11:28.334 --> 11:29.959
- Clenna Dolan.

11:30.000 --> 11:32.042
You sent word about her?

11:32.083 --> 11:34.125
- Yes, of course.

11:36.000 --> 11:37.792
- Thank you for dinner.

11:42.626 --> 11:44.542
- I'll keep my eye on that one.

11:44.584 --> 11:48.000
- Do not provoke him

11:44.584 --> 11:48.000
or his men,

11:48.042 --> 11:50.542
and I want the girl here

11:48.042 --> 11:50.542
in the residence.

11:50.584 --> 11:52.167
Have her brought over.

11:53.667 --> 11:55.667
- Tonight?

11:53.667 --> 11:55.667
- No.

11:57.000 --> 11:58.667
Bring her through the town.

11:58.709 --> 12:00.626
Make sure she's well observed.

12:00.667 --> 12:03.000
Word of her presence

12:00.667 --> 12:03.000
will soon travel.

12:03.042 --> 12:06.334
Let's see if the sugar

12:03.042 --> 12:06.334
attracts any wasps.

12:06.375 --> 12:09.959
♪♪♪

12:10.042 --> 12:11.167
- What we need is information:

12:11.209 --> 12:13.209
how many redcoats,

12:11.209 --> 12:13.209
where they're stationed.

12:13.250 --> 12:15.209
- The garrison then,

12:13.250 --> 12:15.209
by the Governor's house.

12:15.250 --> 12:17.334
- We'll get a head count,

12:15.250 --> 12:17.334
their routine,

12:17.375 --> 12:19.375
when they're most likely

12:17.375 --> 12:19.375
to be surprised.

12:19.417 --> 12:21.542
- How exactly are we going

12:19.417 --> 12:21.542
to kill them?

12:21.584 --> 12:23.626
We are only three.

12:21.584 --> 12:23.626
- Gunpowder.

12:23.667 --> 12:25.000
- Gunpowder? How much?

12:25.042 --> 12:26.626
Harp: Ten barrels.

12:26.667 --> 12:28.792
- Where will we get it?

12:26.667 --> 12:28.792
- Leave that to me.

12:28.834 --> 12:30.918
We'll meet at the ale house,

12:28.834 --> 12:30.918
back entrance.

12:30.959 --> 12:33.209
Make sure you're not seen.

12:30.959 --> 12:33.209
The redcoats know your faces.

12:33.250 --> 12:35.292
If they see you they will shoot.

12:35.334 --> 12:37.500
Garrison's that way. Good luck.

12:39.500 --> 12:41.876
- (Sighs) Let's go.

12:45.751 --> 12:47.709
Johnson: I require lodging

12:45.751 --> 12:47.709
for my men.

12:47.751 --> 12:50.334
They'll not be on that ship

12:47.751 --> 12:50.334
another night.

12:50.375 --> 12:52.709
- I've found you something

12:50.375 --> 12:52.709
at the edge of town.

12:52.751 --> 12:54.834
It's a former stable.

12:52.751 --> 12:54.834
It's not the cleanest.

12:54.876 --> 12:57.000
Could be a little drafty

12:54.876 --> 12:57.000
in this weather,

12:57.042 --> 12:59.167
but you'll make it work.

12:57.042 --> 12:59.167
- Not acceptable.

12:59.209 --> 13:01.876
You will find room here

12:59.209 --> 13:01.876
with your men.

13:03.083 --> 13:04.918
- (Chuckles)

13:06.959 --> 13:09.375
We may be of equal rank,

13:06.959 --> 13:09.375
Johnson,

13:09.417 --> 13:11.542
but I am in command here

13:11.584 --> 13:13.375
and you report to me,

13:13.417 --> 13:14.834
and you'll be garrisoned

13:14.876 --> 13:17.667
wherever the fuck I say

13:14.876 --> 13:17.667
you'll be garrisoned.

13:19.083 --> 13:22.250
- You will also give me access

13:19.083 --> 13:22.250
to Company ledgers

13:22.292 --> 13:24.834
and a key to the Company

13:22.292 --> 13:24.834
storehouse,

13:24.876 --> 13:27.292
as Lord Fisher has requested.

13:28.751 --> 13:31.250
That means now, Captain.

13:31.292 --> 13:34.083
♪♪♪

13:34.125 --> 13:36.375
- Hmm.

13:36.417 --> 13:38.709
(Receding footsteps)

13:38.751 --> 13:41.250
Coffin: All of my efforts,

13:41.292 --> 13:42.959
my struggles...

13:43.959 --> 13:46.209
pursued by bloodthirsty

13:43.959 --> 13:46.209
Frenchmen,

13:47.209 --> 13:48.918
captured and tortured

13:51.042 --> 13:53.209
by Declan Harp, what a bast--

13:56.542 --> 13:59.959
They have been a test,

13:56.542 --> 13:59.959
do you see?

14:00.000 --> 14:03.292
God... has been leading me

14:00.000 --> 14:03.292
to a kind of epiph...

14:05.209 --> 14:07.542
epiph... epiphany of sorts.

14:09.500 --> 14:11.042
- Which is what, Father?

14:11.083 --> 14:13.500
- Oh, you sweet flower.

14:13.542 --> 14:15.542
What is wine if not joy?

14:17.667 --> 14:19.959
And what is joy if not God?

14:22.083 --> 14:24.792
Ergo - that's Latin -

14:22.083 --> 14:24.792
therefore...

14:26.250 --> 14:28.000
wine is surely God!

14:29.459 --> 14:31.584
(Laughs kiddily)

14:31.626 --> 14:34.334
This is my church!

14:34.375 --> 14:37.000
This ale house, here I stand.

14:37.042 --> 14:39.042
I can do no more.

14:39.083 --> 14:41.417
And these miserable sinners...

14:42.584 --> 14:44.375
are my congregation.

14:44.417 --> 14:45.959
(Door opens)

14:46.000 --> 14:47.876
(Door bangs shut)

14:49.167 --> 14:50.834
- In the back.

14:50.876 --> 14:52.334
(Hurried footsteps thud)

15:00.250 --> 15:02.792
- I need the Company ledger.

15:00.250 --> 15:02.792
Where is it?

15:02.834 --> 15:05.167
- What's happened?

15:02.834 --> 15:05.167
- Did you fix it?

15:05.209 --> 15:07.834
Show me what you did.

15:07.876 --> 15:09.876
- This column records

15:07.876 --> 15:09.876
the incoming pelts.

15:09.918 --> 15:12.417
I made changes here, here.

15:12.459 --> 15:14.334
Nothing that would draw

15:12.459 --> 15:14.334
attention.

15:14.375 --> 15:16.083
- Johnson's doin' an inventory.

15:16.125 --> 15:18.751
He's in the Company storehouse

15:16.125 --> 15:18.751
right now counting pelts.

15:18.792 --> 15:20.000
- Why?

15:20.042 --> 15:23.542
- Orders from London he says.

15:23.584 --> 15:26.125
- Lord Benton is out of favor.

15:26.167 --> 15:29.000
Oh, why else would the Company

15:26.167 --> 15:29.000
send someone?

15:29.042 --> 15:31.876
They're lookin' for an excuse

15:29.042 --> 15:31.876
to sack Benton.

15:31.918 --> 15:33.959
Look, this could be a disaster.

15:34.000 --> 15:36.500
You have to be the next Governor

15:34.000 --> 15:36.500
here, not this Johnson!

15:36.542 --> 15:38.542
- Oh, trust me,

15:36.542 --> 15:38.542
that arrogant fuck

15:38.584 --> 15:40.250
isn't sackin' anyone!

15:40.292 --> 15:42.125
Captain Johnson will sail

15:42.167 --> 15:44.167
before the Bay freezes over,

15:44.209 --> 15:47.042
and if he doesn't

15:44.209 --> 15:47.042
I'll cut his fuckin' throat.

15:48.417 --> 15:50.584
(Chopping sounds

15:48.417 --> 15:50.584
from next room)

15:50.626 --> 15:57.375
♪♪♪

15:57.417 --> 15:59.417
- I've got a job for you.

16:01.334 --> 16:03.083
This new man, Johnson,

16:04.459 --> 16:06.334
you're gonna pay him a visit.

16:07.417 --> 16:09.459
- Ma'am, when I first came

16:07.417 --> 16:09.459
here you said

16:09.500 --> 16:12.167
this wasn't a whorehouse.

16:09.500 --> 16:12.167
- And it's not.

16:12.209 --> 16:14.292
You don't sleep with anyone

16:12.209 --> 16:14.292
if you don't want to,

16:14.334 --> 16:17.000
but he doesn't need

16:14.334 --> 16:17.000
to know that.

16:17.042 --> 16:19.000
I need you to lure

16:17.042 --> 16:19.000
him back here.

16:19.042 --> 16:20.918
- Why?

16:20.959 --> 16:23.918
- Captain Johnson

16:20.959 --> 16:23.918
is a religious man.

16:25.209 --> 16:27.500
I'm gonna use that against him.

16:30.751 --> 16:32.459
(Footsteps thud)

16:35.959 --> 16:38.125
(Muffled scream)

16:35.959 --> 16:38.125
- Shh, shh, shh.

16:38.167 --> 16:40.500
Don't scream. Don't scream.

16:40.542 --> 16:43.417
- (Gasps)

16:43.459 --> 16:46.000
- You tryin' to scare

16:43.459 --> 16:46.000
me to death?

16:47.000 --> 16:48.834
- We need to talk.

16:48.876 --> 16:50.959
Chesterfield: "A full inventory"

16:51.000 --> 16:53.167
his very words,

16:51.000 --> 16:53.167
by the order of Lord Fisher!

16:53.209 --> 16:55.500
He's in the storehouse

16:53.209 --> 16:55.500
right now countin' pelts!

16:55.542 --> 16:56.751
(Ledger bangs down)

16:56.792 --> 16:58.709
He wants to see the ledgers.

17:00.042 --> 17:01.876
- (Sighs)

17:03.459 --> 17:05.751
(Ledgers bang down)

17:05.792 --> 17:08.375
Send them over.

17:08.417 --> 17:10.751
We shall allow this

17:08.417 --> 17:10.751
Captain Johnson

17:10.792 --> 17:13.459
to play his game for now.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.459
(Sucks his teeth)

17:15.500 --> 17:17.626
And the girl? Young Clenna?

17:17.667 --> 17:20.792
- She's on her way, sir,

17:17.667 --> 17:20.792
as we speak.

17:20.834 --> 17:27.876
♪♪♪

17:27.918 --> 17:29.792
Sokanon: Middle of the night,

17:29.834 --> 17:32.000
we come out of the forest

17:29.834 --> 17:32.000
and we work quietly.

17:32.042 --> 17:34.542
Three, maybe four barrels

17:32.042 --> 17:34.542
of gunpowder.

17:34.584 --> 17:35.876
That should be enough.

17:35.918 --> 17:37.959
We place them at the back

17:35.918 --> 17:37.959
behind the tents,

17:38.000 --> 17:39.751
there out of sight.

17:39.792 --> 17:41.292
- Can I ask you somethin'?

17:41.334 --> 17:44.042
Do you think we're mad taking

17:41.334 --> 17:44.042
on Lord Benton and the HBC?

17:45.167 --> 17:48.584
- Scared?

17:45.167 --> 17:48.584
- No.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.292
Sort of, ya.

17:52.334 --> 17:54.542
- You should be.

17:54.584 --> 17:56.626
You're terrible at fighting.

17:56.667 --> 17:58.125
You'll be the first to die.

17:58.167 --> 17:59.876
- (Small snicker)

17:59.918 --> 18:02.667
Then I guess you'll have

17:59.918 --> 18:02.667
to train me, won't ya?

18:02.709 --> 18:05.250
- Mmm, take too much time.

18:09.000 --> 18:11.167
- You know, you've a really

18:09.000 --> 18:11.167
dark fuckin' sense of humor

18:11.209 --> 18:14.209
and I can't decide if I hate it

18:11.209 --> 18:14.209
or if like it.

18:16.417 --> 18:19.167
Soldier: This way, love,

18:16.417 --> 18:19.167
come on.

18:19.209 --> 18:21.167
- Christ Almighty!

18:21.209 --> 18:23.417
I can't believe it.

18:21.209 --> 18:23.417
They brought her over!

18:23.459 --> 18:25.000
- Who?

18:25.042 --> 18:27.042
- Clenna!

18:27.083 --> 18:28.542
I have to go.

18:28.584 --> 18:30.459
- Michael!

18:33.167 --> 18:34.876
(Approaching footsteps)

18:34.918 --> 18:37.167
(Knock at the door)

18:37.209 --> 18:38.542
- (Fearful gasp)

18:38.584 --> 18:41.667
- Oh, my dear, there's

18:38.584 --> 18:41.667
no reason to be afraid.

18:43.167 --> 18:46.459
Oh, have you been mistreated

18:43.167 --> 18:46.459
on the voyage?

18:46.500 --> 18:48.500
Oh, you poor, dear girl.

18:49.584 --> 18:51.375
Well, see here,

18:52.626 --> 18:54.626
look what I've brought you.

18:57.167 --> 18:59.209
Go on.

19:00.375 --> 19:02.792
Plenty more downstairs

19:00.375 --> 19:02.792
in the kitchen.

19:02.834 --> 19:05.083
You must help yourself.

19:05.125 --> 19:08.209
It gets cold in this room

19:05.125 --> 19:08.209
at night,

19:08.250 --> 19:10.751
but you have plenty of furs

19:08.250 --> 19:10.751
to keep you warm,

19:10.792 --> 19:14.709
and we shall find you a bath

19:10.792 --> 19:14.709
and some clean clothes, yes.

19:16.500 --> 19:18.250
- And in return?

19:18.292 --> 19:19.751
I know about men like you,

19:19.792 --> 19:22.125
you take what you want

19:19.792 --> 19:22.125
from girls like me.

19:22.167 --> 19:24.209
- Good heavens, no!

19:24.250 --> 19:27.500
Well, I simply enjoy

19:24.250 --> 19:27.500
the company of women.

19:27.542 --> 19:29.792
If they are young and lovely

19:29.834 --> 19:31.709
then so much the better.

19:31.751 --> 19:34.792
So, you will dine

19:31.751 --> 19:34.792
with me tonight

19:34.834 --> 19:37.167
and nothing more.

19:37.209 --> 19:39.792
You are my guest

19:37.209 --> 19:39.792
and under my protection.

19:42.542 --> 19:46.000
With any luck you may even

19:42.542 --> 19:46.000
see your young man again.

19:46.042 --> 19:47.584
- Michael?

19:47.626 --> 19:49.209
Is he, is he here?!

19:49.250 --> 19:51.375
- I'm afraid not, my dear.

19:51.417 --> 19:54.626
He's been captured by a savage,

19:51.417 --> 19:54.626
Declan Harp.

19:56.209 --> 19:58.042
He's in terrible danger.

19:58.083 --> 20:00.042
I fear for his life.

20:00.083 --> 20:04.083
But if he learns you've arrived

20:00.083 --> 20:04.083
in the New World,

20:04.125 --> 20:07.292
you may just be the key

20:04.125 --> 20:07.292
to his salvation.

20:09.876 --> 20:11.792
Hmm. See you at dinner.

20:12.834 --> 20:14.250
(Receding footsteps)

20:14.292 --> 20:23.292
♪♪♪

20:27.709 --> 20:29.667
(Branches rustle)

20:29.709 --> 20:37.918
♪♪♪

20:37.959 --> 20:40.209
(Dog barks, soldiers chatter,

20:37.959 --> 20:40.209
cart clatters)

20:41.667 --> 20:43.709
(Dog barks, fires crackle)

20:47.167 --> 20:49.667
(Door opens)

20:47.167 --> 20:49.667
- Captain Johnson?

20:50.959 --> 20:52.918
I saw you earlier

20:50.959 --> 20:52.918
at the ale house.

20:52.959 --> 20:55.709
May I come in?

20:52.959 --> 20:55.709
I brought you some supper.

20:55.751 --> 20:57.709
(Door shuts)

20:59.500 --> 21:01.751
- I heard you were

20:59.500 --> 21:01.751
a religious man.

21:01.792 --> 21:03.584
I admire that.

21:03.626 --> 21:05.834
I didn't bring you wine or ale,

21:03.626 --> 21:05.834
just water.

21:05.876 --> 21:08.000
I think you'll find it

21:05.876 --> 21:08.000
quite refreshing.

21:08.042 --> 21:10.584
- Very kind. Thank you.

21:10.626 --> 21:12.584
(Grunts with effort)

21:12.626 --> 21:15.375
- Good heavens, have you been

21:12.626 --> 21:15.375
lifting all those bales?

21:15.417 --> 21:18.125
You must be in excellent health.

21:18.167 --> 21:20.250
You certainly look to be.

21:20.292 --> 21:22.209
- I... yes.

21:24.209 --> 21:26.209
- In my previous life

21:24.209 --> 21:26.209
back in London

21:26.250 --> 21:28.000
I knew lots of soldiers,

21:29.083 --> 21:31.083
but I never met one quite

21:29.083 --> 21:31.083
as endowed

21:31.125 --> 21:33.292
with your immense gifts.

21:33.334 --> 21:35.417
I'll do anything you want,

21:33.334 --> 21:35.417
Captain,

21:35.459 --> 21:38.167
anything you can imagine...

21:38.209 --> 21:39.375
- That's enough!

21:40.459 --> 21:42.751
I am a man of God,

21:42.792 --> 21:45.042
and an officer

21:42.792 --> 21:45.042
in the British Army!

21:45.083 --> 21:47.417
Please. Go. Now!

21:51.918 --> 21:53.500
(Receding footsteps)

21:53.542 --> 21:55.167
(Door shuts)

21:55.209 --> 21:56.209
(Sighs)

21:56.250 --> 21:58.083
Emberly: His name's Johnson.

21:58.125 --> 22:00.500
He arrived with a company

21:58.125 --> 22:00.500
of soldiers,

22:00.542 --> 22:03.542
unexpectedly as far

22:00.542 --> 22:03.542
as I can tell.

22:03.584 --> 22:06.083
- So altogether...

22:06.125 --> 22:08.000
- In the garrison?

22:08.042 --> 22:10.584
Well, over a hundred men.

22:10.626 --> 22:12.667
- I need gunpowder.

22:12.709 --> 22:14.542
Ten barrels, maybe more.

22:14.584 --> 22:16.834
- Why?

22:16.876 --> 22:18.209
- I was gonna throw you a party

22:18.250 --> 22:20.209
but now you've ruined it.

22:22.751 --> 22:25.209
Gracie, I need this.

22:28.459 --> 22:30.751
- Harp, I run an ale house.

22:30.792 --> 22:33.250
What the hell do I know

22:30.792 --> 22:33.250
about gunpowder?

22:33.292 --> 22:35.876
- Every thief and black

22:33.292 --> 22:35.876
marketeer comes to Fort James

22:35.918 --> 22:38.542
to drink and boast... here.

22:35.918 --> 22:38.542
(Hatchet thuds on table)

22:38.584 --> 22:39.876
I need a name.

22:39.918 --> 22:41.876
- Ten barrels of gunpowder?

22:41.918 --> 22:44.459
- Maybe more.

22:41.918 --> 22:44.459
(Hatchet thuds down)

22:47.167 --> 22:49.709
- What are you thinkin'?

22:49.751 --> 22:51.375
Are you gonna attack

22:49.751 --> 22:51.375
the garrison?

22:51.417 --> 22:52.751
- I'm not going to tell you

22:52.792 --> 22:55.000
'cause I don't want to put

22:52.792 --> 22:55.000
you in danger.

22:55.042 --> 22:57.083
- Fine! Then I'm not gonna

22:55.042 --> 22:57.083
help you.

22:57.125 --> 22:59.459
And there's the door!

22:59.500 --> 23:01.876
Declan, how long

22:59.500 --> 23:01.876
have you known me?!

23:01.918 --> 23:04.459
- (Sighs heavily)

23:01.918 --> 23:04.459
- Seven years? Eight?

23:05.626 --> 23:07.626
When your wife and son were...

23:10.083 --> 23:13.083
You spent weeks upstairs

23:10.083 --> 23:13.083
in that room.

23:14.959 --> 23:17.083
You wouldn't eat.

23:17.125 --> 23:19.375
I fed you brandy.

23:20.876 --> 23:22.834
Declan...

23:26.250 --> 23:29.083
it's time you started

23:26.250 --> 23:29.083
to trust me.

23:29.125 --> 23:30.959
Every minute of every day

23:33.834 --> 23:36.834
you dream about killing

23:33.834 --> 23:36.834
Lord Benton.

23:38.500 --> 23:42.292
You lie awake at night thinkin'

23:38.500 --> 23:42.292
how you might do it.

23:43.500 --> 23:45.292
First you'd slit him open,

23:46.834 --> 23:48.792
down the front,

23:49.876 --> 23:52.417
while he's still alive,

23:49.876 --> 23:52.417
still breathin'.

23:55.500 --> 23:57.626
Then you'd gut him,

23:57.667 --> 24:00.083
his lungs would still

23:57.667 --> 24:00.083
be inflating,

24:00.125 --> 24:02.417
his heart still beating.

24:03.876 --> 24:06.417
He'd be screaming for mercy.

24:09.542 --> 24:11.459
Am I close?

24:14.167 --> 24:16.083
- Yes.

24:17.334 --> 24:20.459
- And you think that'll make

24:17.334 --> 24:20.459
you feel better?

24:22.083 --> 24:24.250
That it'll bring you peace?

24:25.334 --> 24:27.709
- It will bring me peace.

24:27.751 --> 24:33.876
♪♪♪

24:33.918 --> 24:35.959
(Knock at the door)

24:36.000 --> 24:37.667
Mary: Excuse me, ma'am.

24:37.709 --> 24:40.375
- What is it?

24:40.417 --> 24:43.876
- There's somebody at the back

24:40.417 --> 24:43.876
door asking for Mr. Harp.

24:43.918 --> 24:46.000
(Weapons clank)

24:46.042 --> 24:47.709
(Footsteps thud)

24:49.500 --> 24:51.459
Michael: She's at the back

24:49.500 --> 24:51.459
of the house.

24:51.500 --> 24:53.459
There's a window.

24:51.500 --> 24:53.459
We could get her out,

24:53.500 --> 24:55.542
just the three of us,

24:53.500 --> 24:55.542
quick and easy!

24:55.584 --> 24:58.542
- You're sure it was Clenna?

24:55.584 --> 24:58.542
- Yes, I'm sure.

24:58.584 --> 25:00.709
- We saw her.

24:58.584 --> 25:00.709
- She's not safe there!

25:00.751 --> 25:03.125
I betrayed Lord Benton for you.

25:00.751 --> 25:03.125
He'll punish her for that!

25:03.167 --> 25:05.876
We have to get her out!

25:03.167 --> 25:05.876
- And what happens then?

25:05.918 --> 25:08.584
An Irish city girl

25:05.918 --> 25:08.584
with us in the wild?

25:08.626 --> 25:10.250
She wouldn't last a day.

25:10.292 --> 25:12.083
- I did!

25:14.500 --> 25:16.042
I'm askin'.

25:16.083 --> 25:17.834
Do it for me.

25:20.709 --> 25:22.500
- (Sighs)

25:25.167 --> 25:26.959
Not tonight.

25:28.167 --> 25:30.209
Both of you go back

25:28.167 --> 25:30.209
to the garrison,

25:30.250 --> 25:31.751
you keep watch.

25:33.000 --> 25:35.000
- Harp, I know--

25:33.000 --> 25:35.000
- Michael...

25:36.125 --> 25:38.626
you said I could trust you.

25:42.959 --> 25:45.000
(Receding footsteps, door opens)

25:47.542 --> 25:49.792
He's gonna go after her.

25:47.542 --> 25:49.792
(Door closes)

25:49.834 --> 25:52.292
- Let him.

25:52.334 --> 25:54.083
He'll come back to us.

25:55.250 --> 25:57.209
Michael Smyth would die for you!

25:59.709 --> 26:03.250
(Receding footsteps,

25:59.709 --> 26:03.250
door opens and closes)

26:07.542 --> 26:10.334
- I'll make it happen,

26:07.542 --> 26:10.334
the gunpowder.

26:11.584 --> 26:13.626
Just get me the silver.

26:14.918 --> 26:17.042
- Thank you.

26:18.417 --> 26:20.417
- There's one condition:

26:22.375 --> 26:24.542
you tell me the truth.

26:24.584 --> 26:27.751
Whatever you're plannin',

26:24.584 --> 26:27.751
I want to know about it.

26:27.792 --> 26:30.250
(Fire crackles)

26:31.792 --> 26:33.500
(Brush rustles)

26:33.542 --> 26:37.709
♪♪♪

26:37.751 --> 26:39.667
(Fire crackles)

26:41.626 --> 26:43.834
(Door opens and closes)

26:46.542 --> 26:48.542
Soldier: You see that girl

26:46.542 --> 26:48.542
up there?

26:48.584 --> 26:50.667
Soldier 2: Yeah,

26:48.584 --> 26:50.667
she ain't half bad.

26:50.709 --> 26:58.250
♪♪♪

26:58.292 --> 27:00.375
(Door squeaks open)

27:00.417 --> 27:09.417
♪♪♪

27:10.751 --> 27:13.125
(Floorboards creak)

27:13.167 --> 27:14.709
(Door opens)

27:18.876 --> 27:20.626
(Door clicks closed)

27:22.584 --> 27:23.876
(Happy sigh)

27:25.584 --> 27:26.834
(Rustling sound)

27:26.876 --> 27:28.918
- Shh shh!

27:26.876 --> 27:28.918
- Michael, is that you?!

27:28.959 --> 27:30.292
- Shh!

27:30.334 --> 27:33.500
Are you all right?

27:33.542 --> 27:34.959
(Hard slap)

27:39.292 --> 27:40.667
(Emotional gasps)

27:41.834 --> 27:43.417
I saw you on the road.

27:43.459 --> 27:44.918
I couldn't believe me eyes.

27:44.959 --> 27:46.626
I thought you were still

27:44.959 --> 27:46.626
in London.

27:46.667 --> 27:48.792
I thought of you every day,

27:46.667 --> 27:48.792
Clenna, every minute.

27:48.834 --> 27:50.751
I dreamed of you,

27:48.834 --> 27:50.751
I dreamed of you.

27:50.792 --> 27:54.083
- Me too, I-I... I thought

27:50.792 --> 27:54.083
I'd never see you again.

27:54.125 --> 27:57.542
♪♪♪

27:57.584 --> 28:00.584
(Passionate kisses,

27:57.584 --> 28:00.584
heavy breathing)

28:00.626 --> 28:02.626
- We can't stay here.

28:00.626 --> 28:02.626
We have to go.

28:02.667 --> 28:04.876
- Well, did anyone see

28:02.667 --> 28:04.876
you come in?!

28:04.918 --> 28:07.167
- No.

28:04.918 --> 28:07.167
- Then what's the rush?

28:07.209 --> 28:10.125
They're all sleeping.

28:07.209 --> 28:10.125
Nobody knows you're here.

28:10.167 --> 28:11.584
(Passionate kiss)

28:11.626 --> 28:14.000
Where have you been sleepin'?

28:14.042 --> 28:17.584
You stink like sweat and smoke

28:17.626 --> 28:19.334
and God knows what.

28:20.709 --> 28:21.792
(Stumbling footsteps)

28:21.834 --> 28:24.209
Take off your clothes!

28:24.250 --> 28:29.918
♪♪♪

28:29.959 --> 28:31.709
(Water pours)

28:35.876 --> 28:38.250
Like I said.

28:38.292 --> 28:40.500
Filthy.

28:42.751 --> 28:44.834
(Tender kiss)

28:48.083 --> 28:52.209
♪♪♪

28:52.250 --> 28:56.459
(Animals bay)

28:56.500 --> 28:58.500
- He's actually been brilliant.

28:58.542 --> 29:00.500
He's given me all this,

29:00.542 --> 29:02.459
whatever I want, he says.

29:02.500 --> 29:04.709
At dinner he was a total

29:02.500 --> 29:04.709
gentleman.

29:04.751 --> 29:07.334
I keep waitin' for him

29:04.751 --> 29:07.334
to turn up in his nightshirt,

29:07.375 --> 29:09.334
but it hasn't happened yet.

29:09.375 --> 29:11.417
- I promise you, Clenna,

29:09.375 --> 29:11.417
you can't trust him.

29:13.500 --> 29:15.459
What did he tell ya?

29:13.500 --> 29:15.459
(Belt clinks)

29:15.500 --> 29:17.459
- That you'd been captured

29:15.500 --> 29:17.459
by Harp.

29:17.500 --> 29:19.375
That he's a terrible savage,

29:19.417 --> 29:21.918
and that you'd been seduced

29:19.417 --> 29:21.918
by the devil.

29:21.959 --> 29:23.542
- We're not safe here.

29:23.584 --> 29:25.584
You need to get dressed

29:23.584 --> 29:25.584
and we have to go!

29:25.626 --> 29:27.417
- Go where exactly? Out there?

29:27.459 --> 29:30.584
- Lord Benton's been

29:27.459 --> 29:30.584
lying to you.

29:30.626 --> 29:31.918
I'll explain it all later.

29:31.959 --> 29:33.959
- Michael, I'm not going

29:31.959 --> 29:33.959
out there.

29:34.000 --> 29:36.375
There's wolves out there.

29:36.417 --> 29:37.792
- What?

29:37.834 --> 29:39.209
- Wolves.

29:39.250 --> 29:41.751
Lord Benton told me about them.

29:39.250 --> 29:41.751
I heard them howling.

29:43.334 --> 29:44.834
(Sharp click)

29:44.876 --> 29:46.209
- You're asleep! You're asleep!

29:46.250 --> 29:48.542
Not a sound.

29:46.250 --> 29:48.542
(Door opens)

29:48.584 --> 29:57.584
♪♪♪

30:02.792 --> 30:11.792
♪♪♪

30:13.792 --> 30:16.209
(Receding footsteps, door shuts)

30:22.626 --> 30:24.751
- Tomorrow, meet me

30:22.626 --> 30:24.751
in the forest!

30:24.792 --> 30:26.375
Take the path behind the house.

30:26.417 --> 30:28.667
- Michael, wait!

30:28.709 --> 30:31.042
- If Benton finds me here

30:28.709 --> 30:31.042
he'll kill me,

30:31.083 --> 30:34.250
and God knows what would

30:31.083 --> 30:34.250
happen to you.

30:34.292 --> 30:35.876
Meet me in the forest.

30:35.918 --> 30:37.792
(Passionate kiss)

30:39.500 --> 30:41.167
(Window clatters)

30:41.209 --> 30:43.167
(Clattering bangs) (Grunts)

30:43.209 --> 30:44.876
- Don't break your legs.

30:44.918 --> 30:46.334
- (Breathing hard)

30:46.375 --> 30:48.375
You're really quite lovely.

30:48.417 --> 30:50.542
(Hard thump)

30:50.584 --> 30:53.542
♪♪♪

30:53.584 --> 30:55.792
(Running footsteps)

30:55.834 --> 30:59.876
♪♪♪

30:59.918 --> 31:02.876
- Hello, Michael Smyth.

31:02.918 --> 31:09.167
♪♪♪

31:09.209 --> 31:11.918
(Voices quietly murmur)

31:11.959 --> 31:14.334
(Approaching footsteps)

31:20.250 --> 31:22.250
- Madame Carruthers,

31:22.292 --> 31:24.292
I'm sorry for your loss.

31:24.334 --> 31:25.876
- Mr. Brown.

31:27.918 --> 31:30.667
You've come to pay

31:27.918 --> 31:30.667
your respects, to pray?

31:37.834 --> 31:40.209
- Your husband was a good man.

31:40.250 --> 31:42.834
I-I was there when

31:40.250 --> 31:42.834
it happened, you know.

31:53.250 --> 31:56.417
I have a message

31:53.250 --> 31:56.417
from Samuel Grant.

31:56.459 --> 31:59.042
He wishes to speak with you

31:56.459 --> 31:59.042
about your husband's business.

32:01.542 --> 32:05.417
- Was it not Grant's man

32:01.542 --> 32:05.417
that pulled the trigger?

32:05.459 --> 32:07.584
- Aye, it was.

32:08.834 --> 32:10.792
He feels badly.

32:10.834 --> 32:13.918
His only wish is to meet

32:10.834 --> 32:13.918
with you, that's all.

32:18.000 --> 32:19.918
((Pensive sigh)

32:19.959 --> 32:21.959
- Truthfully, Mr. Brown,

32:23.459 --> 32:26.125
I didn't care much

32:23.459 --> 32:26.125
for my husband.

32:26.167 --> 32:28.792
He was a wretched man.

32:28.834 --> 32:31.667
It's a relief he's gone.

32:31.709 --> 32:34.626
Now I can run

32:31.709 --> 32:34.626
the business properly.

32:34.667 --> 32:37.500
You tell your Mr. Grant

32:34.667 --> 32:37.500
that if he wants my company

32:37.542 --> 32:39.709
he'll have to murder me too.

32:41.417 --> 32:42.792
- Elizabeth.

32:42.834 --> 32:45.125
- What's he got over you,

32:42.834 --> 32:45.125
Mr. Brown?

32:45.167 --> 32:46.876
It must be substantial

32:46.918 --> 32:49.417
for you to come to the funeral

32:46.918 --> 32:49.417
and prey on the widow.

32:51.334 --> 32:53.209
(Receding footsteps)

33:00.626 --> 33:03.125
(Dogs bark, townspeople chatter)

33:03.167 --> 33:05.709
Imogen: I need your help

33:03.167 --> 33:05.709
with Captain Johnson.

33:05.751 --> 33:08.375
I tried to tempt him

33:05.751 --> 33:08.375
but he wouldn't bite.

33:08.417 --> 33:10.751
I thought maybe if there

33:08.417 --> 33:10.751
were two of us.

33:10.792 --> 33:13.667
- Is that what you thought?

33:13.709 --> 33:15.209
- I know you don't like me,

33:13.709 --> 33:15.209
Mary,

33:15.250 --> 33:16.751
but I'm not goin' anywhere.

33:16.792 --> 33:18.876
We might as well work together.

33:18.918 --> 33:20.250
(Patrons chatter)

33:22.918 --> 33:25.000
Okay. Never mind.

33:27.000 --> 33:29.000
- It's better if I go alone.

33:30.500 --> 33:33.459
You played the whore

33:30.500 --> 33:33.459
and it didn't work, so...

33:37.083 --> 33:39.125
Let's try the virgin.

33:45.667 --> 33:47.500
(Cart clatters,

33:45.667 --> 33:47.500
townspeople chatter)

33:52.542 --> 33:54.334
(Door opens)

33:54.375 --> 33:56.667
- Captain Johnson?

33:56.709 --> 33:59.167
- You are?

33:56.709 --> 33:59.167
- Mary, sir.

33:59.209 --> 34:02.667
I brought you some

33:59.209 --> 34:02.667
meat pie and cider.

34:02.709 --> 34:04.167
(Door bangs shut)

34:10.042 --> 34:13.334
- I hope you weren't offended...

34:10.042 --> 34:13.334
by the other girl, I mean.

34:13.375 --> 34:15.125
She can be very forward.

34:15.167 --> 34:16.792
It's hardly appropriate,

34:16.834 --> 34:18.834
especially for a Christian man

34:16.834 --> 34:18.834
like yourself.

34:18.876 --> 34:20.626
- That's quite all right.

34:20.667 --> 34:24.000
Mary: She won't stop

34:20.667 --> 34:24.000
talking about you,

34:24.042 --> 34:26.042
how handsome you are.

34:26.083 --> 34:27.834
She's quite indecent.

34:27.876 --> 34:30.125
I'll be back for the plates

34:27.876 --> 34:30.125
after my prayers,

34:30.167 --> 34:32.459
or, if you like,

34:32.500 --> 34:34.500
bring them yourself

34:32.500 --> 34:34.500
to the ale house.

34:34.542 --> 34:37.209
Miss Emberly is very particular.

34:39.042 --> 34:41.125
- What was your name again?

34:41.167 --> 34:42.959
- Mary, sir.

34:44.918 --> 34:46.751
(Clears his throat)

34:46.792 --> 34:48.542
(Coin clinks)

34:50.834 --> 34:52.167
Mary,

34:52.209 --> 34:54.542
let's not interrupt

34:52.209 --> 34:54.542
your prayers.

34:54.584 --> 34:57.042
I'll see you later then,

34:57.083 --> 34:58.500
at the ale house.

34:58.542 --> 35:00.292
- That'd be wonderful.

35:00.334 --> 35:02.000
(Coins clink)

35:02.042 --> 35:03.334
God bless you.

35:04.375 --> 35:06.542
- And God bless you.

35:12.500 --> 35:14.417
Rivard: The letter is for

35:12.500 --> 35:14.417
Mister Grant.

35:14.459 --> 35:17.042
As you can see,

35:14.459 --> 35:17.042
the seal is unbroken.

35:17.083 --> 35:19.042
Ah, ah, no, no!

35:17.083 --> 35:19.042
It's, it's not for you.

35:19.083 --> 35:20.751
It's for Mr. Grant.

35:20.792 --> 35:22.417
- Shh, I'm reading.

35:23.500 --> 35:25.834
- Mister Grant was uh, no doubt,

35:25.876 --> 35:28.876
expecting me to arrive

35:25.876 --> 35:28.876
with Declan Harp.

35:28.918 --> 35:30.626
It's a troubling story.

35:30.667 --> 35:33.167
I go back to the North.

35:30.667 --> 35:33.167
Where is he? Nowhere!

35:33.209 --> 35:34.876
I'm not happy about him.

35:34.918 --> 35:36.500
- Grace Emberly?

35:36.542 --> 35:38.209
- Oh, oui, monsieur.

35:38.250 --> 35:40.751
She operates the ale house.

35:40.792 --> 35:42.292
A beautiful woman.

35:42.334 --> 35:44.250
Also a shrewd woman.

35:44.292 --> 35:45.876
Good with business.

35:45.918 --> 35:48.334
Uh, whatever she says there I...

35:45.918 --> 35:48.334
I don't know,

35:48.375 --> 35:52.000
she doesn't tell me,

35:48.375 --> 35:52.000
but you may believe it.

35:52.042 --> 35:54.542
What is it exactly

35:52.042 --> 35:54.542
that she says?

35:54.584 --> 35:58.584
- We have been receiving a lot

35:54.584 --> 35:58.584
of news from the North.

35:58.626 --> 36:01.292
Brown Brothers,

35:58.626 --> 36:01.292
the Lake Walkers.

36:02.500 --> 36:04.751
It's a very chaotic place

36:02.500 --> 36:04.751
it seems.

36:04.792 --> 36:06.667
- Well, you know what they say,

36:04.792 --> 36:06.667
monsieur:

36:06.709 --> 36:08.667
In chaos lies opportunity, hmm?

36:10.542 --> 36:14.375
- And I suppose Declan Harp is

36:10.542 --> 36:14.375
taking advantage of this chaos.

36:14.417 --> 36:15.959
- Who can say?

36:16.000 --> 36:17.667
Declan Harp is a crazy person.

36:17.709 --> 36:19.751
He comes, he goes.

36:19.792 --> 36:22.042
What he is thinking or doing?

36:22.083 --> 36:23.375
Pfft, who knows?

36:23.417 --> 36:25.000
(Nervous chuckle)

36:25.042 --> 36:27.000
- I'm going to give Mr. Grant

36:25.042 --> 36:27.000
this letter

36:27.042 --> 36:29.042
and he's gonna want to compose

36:27.042 --> 36:29.042
a reply, I'm sure,

36:29.083 --> 36:31.584
and you can take that back

36:29.083 --> 36:31.584
to Miss Emberly?

36:31.626 --> 36:33.709
- Oh, you want me to go to

36:31.626 --> 36:33.709
the North?

36:33.751 --> 36:35.250
But I just arrive.

36:35.292 --> 36:37.000
- You'll leave tonight,

36:35.292 --> 36:37.000
monsieur.

36:37.042 --> 36:41.042
- I was thinking maybe a soft

36:37.042 --> 36:41.042
bed, a good steak?! No?!

36:43.292 --> 36:45.334
(China dish rattles)

36:48.459 --> 36:50.292
- He's coming!

36:50.334 --> 36:53.125
(Knock on the door,

36:50.334 --> 36:53.125
door opens)

36:53.167 --> 36:55.751
- Captain.

36:53.167 --> 36:55.751
- (Clears his throat)

36:55.792 --> 36:57.209
(Door shuts)

36:59.042 --> 37:00.876
- I'm a...

37:00.918 --> 37:02.584
returning the plate.

37:02.626 --> 37:04.042
- Thank you.

37:04.083 --> 37:06.417
If you don't mind just bringing

37:04.083 --> 37:06.417
it right through here.

37:06.459 --> 37:08.459
I'll just be a moment.

37:10.000 --> 37:11.292
(Curtain rustles)

37:12.751 --> 37:14.876
Good work, both of you.

37:14.918 --> 37:17.042
Now get him into

37:14.918 --> 37:17.042
a compromising position,

37:17.083 --> 37:18.876
but be careful.

37:22.334 --> 37:24.250
- (Clears throat daintily)

37:25.709 --> 37:27.209
I'll take that.

37:29.083 --> 37:30.959
Kind of you to return it.

37:32.125 --> 37:33.500
(China dish clinks)

37:34.542 --> 37:37.125
Captain Johnson,

37:37.167 --> 37:40.083
I have a confession.

37:40.125 --> 37:42.209
- Uh, um...

37:42.250 --> 37:43.918
Please.

37:45.375 --> 37:49.459
- Since we spoke, before

37:45.375 --> 37:49.459
I've been feeling very...

37:49.500 --> 37:51.375
peculiar.

37:52.542 --> 37:54.876
The thoughts in my head are...

37:54.918 --> 37:56.834
sinful.

37:56.876 --> 38:00.250
Extremely sinful

37:56.876 --> 38:00.250
and I feel very ashamed.

38:05.167 --> 38:08.209
Do you ever have thoughts

38:05.167 --> 38:08.209
like this?

38:08.250 --> 38:11.542
- Um, upon occasion.

38:13.834 --> 38:15.918
The um...

38:15.959 --> 38:17.834
the flesh is... tempting.

38:18.876 --> 38:21.292
- What do you do, Captain,

38:21.334 --> 38:23.918
when the temptation's...

38:23.959 --> 38:26.250
(Breathes shakily)

38:23.959 --> 38:26.250
overwhelming...

38:29.042 --> 38:31.167
and it fills you entirely?

38:32.542 --> 38:34.292
(Cloak flutters down)

38:35.876 --> 38:37.876
- We, uh, must pray.

38:39.709 --> 38:41.834
Together.

38:46.167 --> 38:48.209
(Soft kiss)

38:52.626 --> 38:55.167
(Firmer kiss)

38:55.209 --> 38:57.292
- (Breathes passionately)

38:58.834 --> 39:00.334
(Passionate kisses)

39:04.167 --> 39:06.292
(Passionate breathing,

39:04.167 --> 39:06.292
lusting gasps)

39:08.792 --> 39:10.417
(Stuttering breaths)

39:12.542 --> 39:14.792
(Belt clatters,

39:12.542 --> 39:14.792
passionate breathing)

39:16.000 --> 39:18.375
(Stumbling steps)

39:16.000 --> 39:18.375
Coffin: Oh!

39:18.417 --> 39:19.959
- Father!

39:20.000 --> 39:22.209
- My son, what are you...?

39:22.250 --> 39:24.417
Oh. Oh ho ho oh, disgusting!

39:25.834 --> 39:27.375
- Mary, out now!

39:28.584 --> 39:30.417
I don't know where

39:28.584 --> 39:30.417
you think you are,

39:30.459 --> 39:32.751
but this is a decent

39:30.459 --> 39:32.751
establishment

39:32.792 --> 39:34.876
for good Christian people!

39:34.918 --> 39:36.375
It is not a whorehouse.

39:36.417 --> 39:38.876
- That woman, she seduced me!

39:38.918 --> 39:41.083
- Oh, don't embarrass yourself,

39:38.918 --> 39:41.083
Captain,

39:41.125 --> 39:43.834
I know exactly

39:41.125 --> 39:43.834
what happened here

39:43.876 --> 39:47.083
and I know exactly who you are.

39:47.125 --> 39:49.167
You're a sinner.

39:49.209 --> 39:51.209
A wretch.

39:52.459 --> 39:56.375
Trust me. You do not want

39:52.459 --> 39:56.375
to take me on, sir.

39:59.584 --> 40:01.500
- You'll keep this to yourself?

40:03.626 --> 40:06.250
- I will, for now.

40:07.918 --> 40:11.626
And I will take care

40:07.918 --> 40:11.626
of Father Coffin.

40:11.667 --> 40:14.167
You may go.

40:14.209 --> 40:15.876
- (Breathing hard)

40:22.375 --> 40:24.083
Imogen: The priest

40:22.375 --> 40:24.083
was a nice touch.

40:24.125 --> 40:25.542
Mary: Yeah,

40:24.125 --> 40:25.542
poor Captain Johnson.

40:25.584 --> 40:27.500
He looked quite mortified.

40:27.542 --> 40:29.459
- Go on back to work,

40:27.542 --> 40:29.459
both of you.

40:29.500 --> 40:38.667
♪♪♪

40:38.709 --> 40:40.375
(Leaves rustle)

40:42.042 --> 40:43.751
Chesterfield: Rumor has it

40:43.792 --> 40:45.959
the Cree are at odds

40:46.000 --> 40:48.000
with Harp and his men.

40:48.042 --> 40:50.792
Benton: And the emissary

40:48.042 --> 40:50.792
we sent with gifts,

40:50.834 --> 40:53.125
Corporal Lockington?

40:53.167 --> 40:55.876
Chesterfield: They dumped him

40:53.167 --> 40:55.876
there burnt to death.

40:55.918 --> 40:59.417
Not a pleasant one

40:55.918 --> 40:59.417
by the looks of it.

40:59.459 --> 41:01.667
Apparently there's a new chief

40:59.459 --> 41:01.667
of the Lake Walkers.

41:01.709 --> 41:03.292
- Indeed.

41:03.334 --> 41:06.125
- And apparently, he doesn't

41:03.334 --> 41:06.125
fucking like us.

41:06.167 --> 41:08.083
- (Sighs heavily)

41:08.125 --> 41:10.167
- Well, we'll have

41:08.125 --> 41:10.167
to march on them.

41:10.209 --> 41:12.500
In winter. Bloody hell!

41:12.542 --> 41:14.751
(Knock at the door)

41:15.834 --> 41:18.292
Oh, what a vision

41:15.834 --> 41:18.292
of loveliness!

41:18.334 --> 41:19.459
- Sorry to interrupt.

41:19.500 --> 41:21.125
- Not at all, my dear.

41:21.167 --> 41:23.542
I trust you slept well?

41:23.584 --> 41:26.417
- You said I could

41:23.584 --> 41:26.417
go for a walk? Some air?

41:26.459 --> 41:27.959
- Yes, of course.

41:28.000 --> 41:31.125
We'll get you some furs

41:28.000 --> 41:31.125
and someone to escort you.

41:31.167 --> 41:33.709
- I don't need an escort.

41:33.751 --> 41:36.250
I won't be goin' far.

41:33.751 --> 41:36.250
I can take care of me self.

41:36.292 --> 41:38.292
Benton: I don't doubt it

41:36.292 --> 41:38.292
for a moment,

41:38.334 --> 41:40.375
but do be careful.

41:40.417 --> 41:43.125
There are many dangers

41:40.417 --> 41:43.125
in the forest.

41:43.167 --> 41:45.459
It isn't safe.

41:58.292 --> 42:00.334
(Birds caw, river flows)

42:00.375 --> 42:02.167
- (Shivering)

42:02.209 --> 42:03.584
(Soft whistles)

42:04.626 --> 42:09.584
♪♪♪

42:09.626 --> 42:11.417
- (Shivering gasp)

42:11.459 --> 42:12.792
Mary Mother of God,

42:12.834 --> 42:14.959
I have never been so cold

42:12.834 --> 42:14.959
in my life!

42:15.000 --> 42:17.125
What, what are you doin'?!

42:15.000 --> 42:17.125
- They'll be following you.

42:17.167 --> 42:19.167
Shh! They'll be following you.

42:17.167 --> 42:19.167
- Why would they follow me?

42:19.209 --> 42:21.209
- 'Cause you're coming to me

42:19.209 --> 42:21.209
and Benton knows that!

42:21.250 --> 42:23.250
- Wait, Michael, stop!

42:21.250 --> 42:23.250
- Shh!

42:23.292 --> 42:26.209
- You've got it all wrong.

42:23.292 --> 42:26.209
Lord Benton is a good man.

42:26.250 --> 42:28.500
He promised that we could

42:26.250 --> 42:28.500
go home to London together,

42:28.542 --> 42:30.918
he talked about a job for you

42:28.542 --> 42:30.918
with the Company.

42:30.959 --> 42:32.500
- No Clenna.

42:32.542 --> 42:34.500
- It's everything we talked

42:32.542 --> 42:34.500
about.

42:34.542 --> 42:36.500
A better life together,

42:34.542 --> 42:36.500
you said so yourself.

42:36.542 --> 42:38.500
- It's all lies.

42:36.542 --> 42:38.500
- No, it isn't!

42:38.542 --> 42:43.375
He told me you might say that.

42:38.542 --> 42:43.375
Wha... He wants to help us.

42:43.417 --> 42:44.626
- No, you have to trust me,

42:43.417 --> 42:44.626
Clenna.

42:44.667 --> 42:47.042
Everything Benton said

42:44.667 --> 42:47.042
is a lie. We have to go!

42:47.083 --> 42:48.751
- Stop, stop!

42:48.792 --> 42:50.751
Last time I followed you,

42:48.792 --> 42:50.751
Michael,

42:50.792 --> 42:53.334
my brother ended up dead,

42:53.375 --> 42:55.834
and I ended up in prison,

42:55.876 --> 42:59.459
and then on a horrible ship

42:55.876 --> 42:59.459
in chains for weeks,

43:01.209 --> 43:03.000
freezing cold and starving

43:04.042 --> 43:06.417
and surrounded by filthy men

43:06.459 --> 43:08.542
with their rotting teeth

43:08.584 --> 43:10.751
and their stinking breath

43:10.792 --> 43:13.209
and all so I could end up here

43:13.250 --> 43:16.209
in this horrible frigid place!

43:16.250 --> 43:19.459
So no, I don't think I will

43:16.250 --> 43:19.459
follow you this time!

43:23.834 --> 43:26.417
What happened to you, Michael?

43:26.459 --> 43:28.167
I don't recognize ya.

43:29.250 --> 43:31.459
I want to go home to London.

43:33.459 --> 43:36.417
I'm not goin' any further

43:33.459 --> 43:36.417
into this madness!

43:36.459 --> 43:38.125
- No. Clenna.

43:38.167 --> 43:44.000
♪♪♪

43:44.042 --> 43:45.542
(Fire crackles)

43:45.584 --> 43:48.209
- We've already waited too long.

43:45.584 --> 43:48.209
Let's go.

43:51.125 --> 43:52.834
He has made his choice, Sokanon.

43:52.876 --> 43:54.667
(Door opens)

43:54.709 --> 43:56.292
(Door shuts)

43:57.626 --> 43:59.626
- I didn't think

43:57.626 --> 43:59.626
you'd still be here.

43:59.667 --> 44:00.834
- What happened?

44:00.876 --> 44:02.834
- Benton's been feeding

44:00.876 --> 44:02.834
her lies.

44:02.876 --> 44:04.876
I couldn't convince

44:02.876 --> 44:04.876
her to leave.

44:04.918 --> 44:07.250
- Are you with us?

44:07.292 --> 44:09.250
- I am.

44:09.292 --> 44:11.626
- Good. It's not safe here.

44:11.667 --> 44:13.709
Let's make camp outside

44:11.667 --> 44:13.709
of town. Let's go!

44:13.751 --> 44:15.250
(Door opens)

44:15.292 --> 44:17.584
♪♪♪

44:17.626 --> 44:19.292
- Soldiers coming.

44:19.334 --> 44:22.250
- They followed you!

44:19.334 --> 44:22.250
- Come on. This way.

